7845133, \"text\": \"Indiana\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indiana_Hoosiers_football\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indiana_Hoosiers_football\"}, {\"begin\": 254, \"end\": 266, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Swimming\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USA Swimming\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Swimming\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Swimming\"}, {\"begin\": 267, \"end\": 281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Olympic_trials_(track_and_field)\", \"score\": 0.8581582794952675, \"rank\": 0.038961038961052005, \"text\": \"Olympic Trials\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Olympic_trials_(track_and_field)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Olympic_trials_(track_and_field)\"}, {\"begin\": 305, \"end\": 317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis\", \"score\": 0.9999999089432136, \"rank\": 4.6268791024931685e-08, \"text\": \"Indianapolis\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alex Shackellbecame the first swimmer from the renowned Carmel High School girls swim program to qualify for the Olympics by finishing second in the women's 200-meter butterfly final.\", \"from\": 320, \"to\": 503, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 320, \"end\": 324, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\", \"score\": 0.9999999999558895, \"rank\": 4.376154977224958e-11, \"text\": \"Alex\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\"}, {\"begin\": 376, \"end\": 394, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carmel_High_School_(Indiana)\", \"score\": 0.670329670221866, \"rank\": 0.22950819672132314, \"text\": \"Carmel High School\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3914\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carmel_High_School_(Indiana)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carmel_High_School_(Indiana)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"AndLilly Kingof the Indiana Swim Club claimed an Olympic spot with a second-place finish in the women's 200 backstroke final right before getting engaged to her boyfriend.\", \"from\": 505, \"to\": 676, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 525, \"end\": 532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indiana_Hoosiers_football\", \"score\": 0.9923697893126527, \"rank\": 0.007488073197845133, \"text\": \"Indiana\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indiana_Hoosiers_football\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indiana_Hoosiers_football\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Also on Thursday,Chris Guilianoof the University of Notre Dame, who hasalready qualified for the Paris Olympicsin the men's 100-meter and 200-meter events, finished first in the semifinals of the 50-meter freestyle, making him a favorite in Friday night's final.\", \"from\": 678, \"to\": 940, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 775, \"end\": 780, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999258762, \"rank\": 7.396656591789509e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Night for doubling up  Ryan Murphy, Regan Smith, Kate Douglass and King all qualified for the Paris Games in a second individual event with their performances Thursday night.\", \"from\": 942, \"to\": 1116, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 965, \"end\": 976, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco_Giants_minor_league_players\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3024017667904495e-15, \"text\": \"Ryan Murphy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco_Giants_minor_league_players\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco_Giants_minor_league_players\"}, {\"begin\": 978, \"end\": 989, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3150412680462965e-42, \"text\": \"Regan Smith\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\"}, {\"begin\": 991, \"end\": 1004, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kate Douglass\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the most dramatic moment came just off the deck when\\u00a0King's boyfriend, former Indiana University swimmer James Wells, pulled out a ring, dropped to a knee and asked her to marry him.\", \"from\": 1118, \"to\": 1304, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1175, \"end\": 1179, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Art_of_Fighting\", \"score\": 0.5502990868483221, \"rank\": 0.798943525036176, \"text\": \"King\", \"types\": [\"Q7889\", \"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Art_of_Fighting\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Art_of_Fighting\"}, {\"begin\": 1200, \"end\": 1218, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indiana_Hoosiers\", \"score\": 0.9382334736726631, \"rank\": 0.063028376614286, \"text\": \"Indiana University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indiana_Hoosiers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indiana_Hoosiers\"}, {\"begin\": 1227, \"end\": 1232, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_VI_and_I\", \"score\": 0.6153234678785663, \"rank\": 0.6118115728552369, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_VI_and_I\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_VI_and_I\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"King, a former IU swimmer from Evansville and Olympic gold medalist, said yes with a kiss and a big hug.\", \"from\": 1306, \"to\": 1410, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1321, \"end\": 1323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indiana_University\", \"score\": 0.8842320212553271, \"rank\": 0.13092421696581893, \"text\": \"IU\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indiana_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indiana_University\"}, {\"begin\": 1337, \"end\": 1347, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Evansville\", \"score\": 0.9999996192837713, \"rank\": 2.378157320001787e-07, \"text\": \"Evansville\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Evansville\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Evansville\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I did not see it,\\\" Murphy said.\", \"from\": 1412, \"to\": 1444, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's unbelievable.\", \"from\": 1445, \"to\": 1466, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I'd love to hear her reaction to how it is to get proposed to completely out of breath and soaked.\", \"from\": 1467, \"to\": 1565, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's incredible.\", \"from\": 1566, \"to\": 1584, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She must be riding an absolute high.\\\"\", \"from\": 1585, \"to\": 1622, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Murphy touched first in the men's 200-meter backstroke, adding to his triumph in the 100 back.\", \"from\": 1624, \"to\": 1718, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Smith won the women's 200 butterfly after previously setting a world record in the 100 backstroke.\", \"from\": 1720, \"to\": 1818, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And Douglass followed up her win a night earlier in the 100 freestyle with a victory in the 200 breaststroke.\", \"from\": 1819, \"to\": 1928, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1823, \"end\": 1831, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stu_Douglass\", \"score\": 0.9980056240410419, \"rank\": 0.001998361442965456, \"text\": \"Douglass\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stu_Douglass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stu_Douglass\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"King rallied to finish behind Douglass, edging Alex Walsh for the second U.S. spot at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1930, \"to\": 2029, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1960, \"end\": 1968, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stu_Douglass\", \"score\": 0.9980056240410419, \"rank\": 0.001998361442965456, \"text\": \"Douglass\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stu_Douglass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stu_Douglass\"}, {\"begin\": 1977, \"end\": 1987, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandra_Walsh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alex Walsh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandra_Walsh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandra_Walsh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"King had previously won the 100 breaststroke.\", \"from\": 2030, \"to\": 2075, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Like brother and father  Smith trailed 17-year-old Alex Shackell in the 200 butterfly at the final turn, but rallied to win in 2:05.70.\", \"from\": 2077, \"to\": 2212, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2128, \"end\": 2132, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\", \"score\": 0.9999999999558895, \"rank\": 4.376154977224958e-11, \"text\": \"Alex\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Shackell, from suburban Carmel, thrilled the home crowd by claiming an Olympic berth in 2:06.69  Shackell is heading to the Olympics with her 19-year-old brother Aaron, who made the team bywinning the 400 freestyleon the opening night of the trials.\", \"from\": 2213, \"to\": 2462, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2237, \"end\": 2243, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carmel_McQueen\", \"score\": 0.999963781588733, \"rank\": 3.6219722991677926e-05, \"text\": \"Carmel\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carmel_McQueen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carmel_McQueen\"}, {\"begin\": 2375, \"end\": 2380, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aaron_Livesy\", \"score\": 0.9944017364369542, \"rank\": 0.005629780449756046, \"text\": \"Aaron\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aaron_Livesy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aaron_Livesy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their father, Nick Shackell, represented Britain at the 1996 and 2000 Olympics.\", \"from\": 2463, \"to\": 2542, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2477, \"end\": 2481, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nick_Jonas\", \"score\": 0.9999961095625811, \"rank\": 3.890017319702135e-06, \"text\": \"Nick\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nick_Jonas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nick_Jonas\"}, {\"begin\": 2504, \"end\": 2511, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9481713882651815, \"rank\": 0.05466161218694569, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Douglass dominated the 200 breaststroke, going out under world-record pace over the first half of the race and finishing in 2:19.46.\", \"from\": 2544, \"to\": 2676, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2544, \"end\": 2552, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stu_Douglass\", \"score\": 0.9980056240410419, \"rank\": 0.001998361442965456, \"text\": \"Douglass\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stu_Douglass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stu_Douglass\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am really happy with both of those wins I have had so far,\\\" Douglass said.\", \"from\": 2678, \"to\": 2755, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2741, \"end\": 2749, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stu_Douglass\", \"score\": 0.9980056240410419, \"rank\": 0.001998361442965456, \"text\": \"Douglass\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stu_Douglass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stu_Douglass\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That was my goal coming into the meet.\", \"from\": 2756, \"to\": 2795, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I was confident in myself, and I am really happy I was able to pull it off.\\\"\", \"from\": 2796, \"to\": 2872, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"King was third at the final turn, but turned up the pace on the final lap for a runner-up finish of 2:21.93.\", \"from\": 2874, \"to\": 2982, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Walsh, a silver medalist in the 200 individual medley at Tokyo Olympics, failed to join her sister Gretchen on this Olympic team.\", \"from\": 2984, \"to\": 3113, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3083, \"end\": 3091, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.712894165105496e-17, \"text\": \"Gretchen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alex Walsh still has a shot to make the squad in the 200 individual medley, which begins Friday.\", \"from\": 3114, \"to\": 3210, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3114, \"end\": 3124, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandra_Walsh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alex Walsh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandra_Walsh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandra_Walsh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Caeleb Dressel bounced back with the second-fastest time in the semifinals of the 50 freestyle, one night after a third-place finish in the 100 free cost him a chance to defend his Olympic title in that event.\", \"from\": 3212, \"to\": 3421, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3212, \"end\": 3226, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caeleb_Dressel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Caeleb Dressel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caeleb_Dressel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caeleb_Dressel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dressel will need to finish in the top two of the 50 free final Friday night to claim his first individual race of the Paris Games.\", \"from\": 3423, \"to\": 3554, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The tattooed Floridian was one of the biggest stars in Tokyo, winning five gold medals, but he has not been as dominant since returning from a long layoff.\", \"from\": 3555, \"to\": 3710, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3568, \"end\": 3577, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.705221098949562e-34, \"text\": \"Floridian\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\"}, {\"begin\": 3610, \"end\": 3615, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999999886313, \"rank\": 7.794052166223428e-12, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There was another bit of drama at the end of the night.\", \"from\": 3712, \"to\": 3767, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After tying for eighth place in the 50 free semifinals, Adam Chaney and Jonny Kulow had a swim-off for the final spot in the final.\", \"from\": 3769, \"to\": 3900, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3830, \"end\": 3836, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Chaney\", \"score\": 0.9372614661819795, \"rank\": 0.06691216320987035, \"text\": \"Chaney\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Chaney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Chaney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But they tied for a second time at 21.79, forcing another swim-off after many fans had headed for the exits.\", \"from\": 3902, \"to\": 4010, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Finally, the matter was settled when Chaney touched in 21.81 to eliminate Kulow, who finished at 21.99.\", \"from\": 4012, \"to\": 4115, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4049, \"end\": 4055, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Chaney\", \"score\": 0.9372614661819795, \"rank\": 0.06691216320987035, \"text\": \"Chaney\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Chaney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Chaney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chaney emphatically splashed the water before reaching over the rope to console Kulow.\", \"from\": 4117, \"to\": 4203, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4117, \"end\": 4123, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Chaney\", \"score\": 0.9372614661819795, \"rank\": 0.06691216320987035, \"text\": \"Chaney\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Chaney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Chaney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Murphy used his stunning underwater technique in the 200-meter backstroke to hold off Keaton Jones and Jack Akins, finishing in 1 minute, 54.33 seconds.\", \"from\": 4205, \"to\": 4357, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4308, \"end\": 4312, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Harkness\", \"score\": 0.9996526882840853, \"rank\": 0.00023384041460043298, \"text\": \"Jack\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Harkness\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Harkness\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He punched the water in triumph when he saw his name atop the scoreboard for the second time in the meet.\", \"from\": 4358, \"to\": 4463, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The last 25, you are just battling,\\\" Murphy said.\", \"from\": 4465, \"to\": 4515, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Nothing feels good the last 25.\", \"from\": 4516, \"to\": 4548, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's like, all right, how can hold this stroke together against the wall, get this done and finish the job?\\\"\", \"from\": 4549, \"to\": 4657, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jones claimed the second spot at the Olympics in 1:54.61, while it was another heartbreaking finish for Akins.\", \"from\": 4659, \"to\": 4769, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He was third in 1:54.78, the same position he had in the 100 backstroke when he missed a Paris berth by two-hundredths of a second.\", \"from\": 4770, \"to\": 4901, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4859, \"end\": 4864, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999258762, \"rank\": 7.396656591789509e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"More Indiana swimmers  In other events involving swimmers with Indiana connections,Tommy Jantonof Notre Dame placed fourth in 200 backstroke final.\", \"from\": 4903, \"to\": 5050, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4908, \"end\": 4915, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indiana_Hoosiers_football\", \"score\": 0.9923697893126527, \"rank\": 0.007488073197845133,